'''Kenneth Nlata Sema''' (born 30 September 1993) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left midfielder]] for [[Cypriot First Division]] club [[Pafos FC|Pafos]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Sema got promoted to the [[IFK Norrköping]] first team as a 19-year old in 2013. However, he spent the entire season on loan to [[IF Sylvia]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nt.se/sport/nio-ifk-spelare-i-sylvias-trupp-8472975.aspx |title=Nio IFK-spelare i Sylvias trupp |first=Ulf |last=Stråhle |date=3 April 2013}}</ref> and did not get his contract renewed after it expired at the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/sema-om-nobben-klart-jag-var-sur/ |title=Sema om nobben: "Klart jag var sur" |website=www.expressen.se|date=13 March 2018 }}</ref>

In 2014, he signed for second-tier team [[Ljungskile SK]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bohuslaningen.se/sport/fotboll/1.2842843-sema-och-bjorlund-klara |archive-url=https://archive.today/20140512223350/http://bohuslaningen.se/sport/fotboll/1.2842843-sema-och-bjorlund-klara |url-status=dead |archive-date=12 May 2014 |title=Sema och Björlund klara}}</ref>

===Östersunds FK===
In January 2016, Sema signed for [[Östersunds FK]] in the [[Allsvenskan]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.op.se/fotboll/allsvenskan/ken-sema-bekraftar-overgangen-till-ofk-jag-ar-klar |title=Ken Sema bekräftar övergången till ÖFK: "Jag är klar" |date=5 January 2016}}</ref> where he would have his major breakthrough. Sema won the [[2016–17 Svenska Cupen]] with Östersund, assisting three of their four goals in the final,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/1lByX |title=Östersund vann Svenska Cupen |date=13 April 2017 |website=www.aftonbladet.se}}</ref> and later played a major role in their [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League]] campaign. On 22 February 2018, Sema scored a goal in a 2–1 win against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the round of 32. Despite this, Östersund were eliminated from the Europa League after losing 2–4 on aggregate.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Arsenal 1-2 Oestersunds FK - UEFA Europa League 2017/2018 Live |work=WhoScored.com |url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1250853/Live/Europe-UEFA-Europa-League-2017-2018-Arsenal-Oestersunds-FK}}</ref>

===Watford===
On 4 July 2018, Östersunds FK chairman Daniel Kindberg revealed that Sema was close to signing for [[Premier League]] club [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.watfordobserver.co.uk/sport/16332898.watford-ostersund-confirm-ken-sema-transfer/ |title=Ostersund confirm Sema's Watford switch |first=Harry |last=Gray |work=Watford Observer |date=4 July 2018}}</ref> The next day, Watford confirmed the signing.<ref>{{cite web |title=Official: Sema Signs On |url=https://www.watfordfc.com/teams/first-team/official-sema-signs |publisher=Watford F.C. |access-date=5 July 2018 |archive-date=26 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180726190450/http://www.watfordfc.com/teams/first-team/official-sema-signs |url-status=dead}}</ref> He scored his first goal against [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] on 2 January 2019 in a 3–3 draw.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Bournemouth and Watford in six-goal thriller |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/46682778 |access-date=2024-03-21 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

He was integral in helping Watford get promoted back to the Premier League in the [[2020–21 Watford F.C. season|2020–21 season]], registering six goals and adding a further six assists.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ken Sema {{!}} Football Stats {{!}} Watford {{!}} Season 2020/2021 {{!}} Soccer Base |url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=89847&season_id=153 |access-date=2024-03-21 |website=www.soccerbase.com}}</ref>

On 6 February 2024, Sema made his 150th appearance for Watford in their [[2023–24 FA Cup|FA Cup]] fourth round replay defeat to [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.watfordfc.com/news/2024/february/8/sema-on-150-milestone-i-m-very-proud-|title=Sema On 150 Milestone: “I'm Very Proud”|website=Watford F.C.|date=8 February 2024|access-date=13 November 2025}}</ref>

On 29 January 2025, Sema departed Watford having had his contract terminated by mutual consent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.watfordfc.com/news/2025/january/29/official-king-ken-departs/|title=Official: Farewell King Ken|website=www.watfordfc.com|date=29 January 2025|accessdate=29 January 2025}}</ref>

====Loan to Udinese====
On 22 August 2019, [[Udinese Calcio]] signed Sema on a season-long loan from Watford.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/watford/watford-winger-ken-sema-completes-udinese-loan-switch-a4219271.html |title=Watford winger Sema completes Udinese loan switch |date=22 August 2019 |website=Evening Standard |language=en |access-date=29 August 2019}}</ref> He made his [[Serie A]] debut for Udinese on 25 August 2019 in a 1–0 win against [[AC Milan]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dn.se/sport/fotboll/vinst-mot-milan-for-sema-i-serie-a-debuten/ |title=Vinst mot Milan för Sema i Serie A-debuten |date=25 August 2019 |website=[[Dagens Nyheter]] |language=sv |access-date=29 August 2019}}</ref>

===Pafos===
On 31 January 2025, Sema signed a contract with [[Cypriot First Division]] club [[Pafos FC|Pafos]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Ken Sema: From Watford FC to Pafos FC! |url=https://pafosfc.com.cy/ken-sema-from-watford-fc-to-pafos-fc/ |website=www.pafosfc.com.cy |publisher= [[Pafos FC|Pafos]] |date=31 January 2025}}</ref> Sema was part of the Pafos side that won the club's first Cypriot league title during the [[2024–25 Cypriot First Division|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cj6x7rrxzedo|title=Pafos FC: Who are Champions League debutants|website=BBC|date=17 September 2025|access-date=18 September 2025}}</ref>

On 5 November 2025, Sema provided the assist for [[Derrick Luckassen]]'s goal in a 1–0 win over [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]]. It was the club's first ever win in the Champions League proper.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c2kppg4n95wt|title=Pafos 1-0 Villarreal: Hosts claim historic first Champions League win|website=BBC|date=5 November 2025|access-date=12 November 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
In 2016, Sema was a part of the [[Sweden national under-23 football team|Sweden Olympic team]] that played in Brazil, and scored his first U23 goal in a match against [[South Korea national under-23 football team|South Korea Olympic]]. In January 2017, he debuted for the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden senior team]] in a friendly 6–0 win over [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com//football/match/2017/jan/12/sweden-v-slovakia |title=Sweden 6 – 0 Slovakia – Football |website=The Guardian}}</ref>

Sema was an unused substitute in [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|the two-legged playoff]] against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in November 2017, which Sweden won, and therefore qualified for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]. Despite featuring in commercials with the rest of the Sweden squad before the World Cup, Sema was eventually left out of the World Cup squad.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/xREJLj |title=Sveriges trupp till fotbolls-VM 2018 – här är alla som får åka till Ryssland |date=15 May 2018 |website=aftonbladet.se}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotbollsvm/jag-kan-forsta-att-det-blir-lite-skevt/ |title=Märkliga Ica-bilderna: "Har blivit reaktioner" |website=expressen.se|date=4 June 2018 }}</ref>

Sema made his competitive international debut in a [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] game against the [[Faroe Islands national football team]] which Sweden won 3–0.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.corren.se/sport/sema-om-em-jakten-maste-jobba-hart-for-det-om6388608.aspx |title=Sema om EM-jakten: "Måste jobba hårt för det" – Corren |date=18 November 2019}}</ref>

He was part of Sweden's squad at [[UEFA Euro 2020]] that reached the round of 16 before being eliminated by [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-05-18 |title=Granqvist och Larsson med i Jannes EM-trupp |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2021/05/granqvist-och-larsson-med-i-jannes-em-trupp/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.svenskfotboll.se |language=sv}}</ref>

On 15 June 2025 he scored a hat-trick in an international friendly against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] which Sweden won 4–3.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c93yxe40kglt |title=Sweden 4 – 3 Algeria – Football |website=BBC}}</ref>

==Playing style==
Sema is known for his hard work, a trait that has made him very popular with Watford fans. He likes to dribble past opponents to get into good crossing positions. He is mainly a winger but has occasionally been used at left back or wing back, due to his ability to work hard and track back defensively. He is affectionately known as King Ken by Watford fans.

==Personal life==
Sema was born in Sweden to [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]] parents, and his brother [[Maic Sema]] is also a footballer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.op.se/fotboll/allsvenskan/ofk-s-nyforvarv-ken-sema-i-stor-intervju-hyllar-foraldrarna-de-flyttade-till-sverige-for-att-ge-sina-barn-ett-bra-liv |title=ÖFK:s nyförvärv Ken Sema i stor intervju – hyllar föräldrarna: "De flyttade till Sverige för att ge sina barn ett bra liv" |first=Patrick |last=Sjöö |date=5 February 2016}}</ref> He speaks with a [[stammer]], and after a video went viral of him doing a post match interview with Watford TV, he was praised as a role model for children and adults with speech impediments.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kemble |first1=Jamie |title=Leeds United's Luke Ayling sends 'love' to Watford star Ken Sema after inspirational interview clip emerges |url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/luke-ayling-sends-love-to-watford-star-ken-sema-after-inspirational-interview-clip-emerges-4035613 |access-date=21 February 2023 |work=Yorkshire Evening |date=21 February 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Browning |first1=Oliver |title=Watford star Ken Sema battles through stammer to give post-match interview |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/tv/sport/football-ken-sema-stammer-watford-b2286772.html |access-date=21 February 2023 |work=Independent |date=21 February 2023}}</ref>

